values: I am having one of those nights when you just can't sleep. It sucks. My boyfriend is snoring away by now and I just want some company. I keep thinking about people I know and the way everything has changed. The ways I have changed. The fact I don't use my apartment enough. LOL (I guess the last one is kind of random) For once in my life things  seem kind of perfect. It is weird and  a little scary. I think I realized the other day how happy i am in love. This time it just feels different than before with any other person. The scare part is thinking of everyone in my past and how easy it is for things to end and change. I don't think we will break up but for the first time in my life I am scared to death of losing him. I feel psychotic. LOL I even had a nightmare last night about losing him and it freaked me out. WOW I sound like a crazy person. It sort of just hit me the other day. I was sitting on the couch talking to him when I thought wow he is my best friend and my boyfriend, and I don't know what i would do without him. I mean I have had guys who were boyfriends before and I have had boyfriend that were more of a best friend than a boyfriend but never the perfect mixture I have now. Ok i guess I am going to sleep now that I have made everyone think I am the cheesiest person ever.

All my life I have been concerned about my future. Probably mostly because of my upbringing. Will I get in to college? When will I finish? Every detail of my life I try to plan out. Is it possible for me to STOP it all and just live in the moment. Can I not worry about the future and if I am doing the right thing? I don't know. I have always been taught to worry about the future, to plan ahead, no surprises but am I forgetting to be happy now? I think if I worry about the future I am going to miss what is in front of me, it is just I don't know how not to think about that stuff.

Not everyday starts out bad that is a bad day. I got up this morning thinking I was going to do wonderful on my physics test. I was over prepare and I was sure that I had studied more than anyone else,  but I got the test and freaked out. I don't really understand what happened because I was sure I knew it all. I just froze and tried to hard I guess. I am really scared about this semester. It just hasn't been the best for me. The sad part is that I am really trying and I am doing worst than people who don't try at all. It makes me really upset. I don't know what to do. I really want to get into med school and I am not going to get in if my GPA keeps dropping. I just really need everyones prayer because I have cried more and been more upset this semester than any semester before. I am just having a really hard time in physics .... aka if anyone wants to help me or tutor me I will be more than glad to pay them because I am desperate. I just really want to past this class and get it over with, and I could use some help in Chemistry too. I think I get the chemistry I am just struggling because my physics is taking up so much of my time. I need help and I need lots of prayer that I don't have a nervous breakdown at the age of 19.

I am usually not a snuggley person except when I really like someone.  I guess that is one of the ways I know I like someone is if I just want to snuggle up next to them and take a nap.  Naps are great they make me feel like an old person who need his or her nap during the day, but that wouldn't be so bad. To be an old person that takes nap during the day. Well anyways my mushy thought for the day.

My bestfriend from high school wrote this about me......


 You were my partner in crime. I've made out in the back of your car(s) with various unnamed individuals. I've lied with you and in spite of you. We are a dynamic duo and I think that we could take over the world with enough petroleum and motivation. You are my favorite person to go out dancing with and to sunbathe with. You laugh at all my jokes and take me seriously when it counts. You never judged me for that chicken wings and Moulin Rogue night or the serious lack of showers. You let me live and explore and covered my butt more times than either of us can possibly remember. You protected my perfect reputation without fail, but you ALWAYS knew truths that no one else ever dreamt of believing. We've had tons of fun. We're growing apart, but I cannot forget. We've cried, laughed, complained, traveled, partied, and puked together. I have no idea how we became friends, but it's been a seriously fantastic trip. What more can I say without bringing up tag-team dating or our Disney channel friend?

I could never meet her skill to write but all I really have to say now it that i will never forget our time together and even though we are growing apart I will still miss her incredible. To the best friend I could ever have.

It is amazing to me how quickly I change my mind. One day I will love being single and the next I am so lonely. Being single isn't easy. I don't ever know how to feel. I think I have grown out of the flirting stage and dating games. I am just not into that anymore. I don't want to play hard to get, and I don't want to enjoy a chase. It isn't fun. Your mind is running crazy wanting to know and you don't. It is actually very depressing. I like being honest. I like knowing how someone feels for me and if someone likes me. If someone doesn't like me I wish they would just not flirt. It hurts to get your hopes up and then realize you have been chasing a dream. Somehow you will never be pretty enough or smart enough or just have that perfect laugh that drives every guy crazy. I want someone to understand me and respect me. I don't want to just make out or be flirty, I want much more. I want passion, caring, understanding, and a friendship that is stronger than any other.  I don't think it is fair that I never get a chance. It seems like if a guy is ever interested in me by the time I find out or start to like him he has found someone new. What happened to the waiting period to give you time to recover. I don't understand the world today and maybe I just never will. I have learned though that it is better to be brave and sorry than to just be sorry and I have learned that I will survive. If I stay at home by myself on Friday night I will be ok. I don't have to have someone; it is nice, but I will keep living with or without it. God will choose my path for me and when he does it will be better than I could ever imagine. So I need to remember to pray. God will listen and he does care!

Everyone always has this idea of a sorority girl as a easy home run but they are so wrong. I work hard. I volunteer and have to keep my grades high. Plus with all the meeting and community service we do, who has time for guys. Now to the positive side. I have been having so much fun this weekend getting gifts from my big sis. I can't wait to find out who she is. Plus, thursday night was squeal night and all the frat boys had to get us gifts too. I really like being in a sorority. I have someone to listen to me when I complain or give me advice on guys. Plus, I know that I am welcome at all times. Some people say you are just buying your friends, but it isn't true. Your sisters do thing for you because they are your friend. All the sorority does is give you a chance to meet these awesome people.
Off of the sorority stuff I have to talk about my awesome and wonderful roommate Kristen. She has become like a best friend. We are always together acting goofy. We are actually planning on rooming together next year too. I have missed my friends back home though. I miss Elizabeth my best friend from high school and tina and erica. I also sorta miss my family but I am completely happy at school and it is so much fun making my own rules for once and being independent.
